## 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

### 4.1 Provider Data Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["ChangeNotifierProvider (Root)"] --> B["CounterNotifier (Holds State)"]
    B --> C["notifyListeners() Triggered"]
    C --> D["Consumer / context.watch Detects"]
    D --> E["Widget Rebuilds with New State"]
    B --> F["context.read() for One-Shot Call"]
    F --> G["Button onPressed Calls increment()"]
    G --> C
```

### 4.2 Riverpod Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["ProviderScope (App Root)"] --> B["counterProvider (StateNotifierProvider)"]
    B --> C["CounterNotifier extends StateNotifier int"]
    C --> D["state = value Triggers Auto-Rebuild"]
    D --> E["ConsumerWidget via ref.watch"]
    C --> F["ref.read in Callbacks"]
    F --> G["Mutate State without Rebuild"]
    H["Tests"] --> I["ProviderContainer (No UI Needed)"]
    B --> I
```

### 4.3 BLoC Event-State Cycle

```mermaid
graph LR
    UI["UI Widget"] -->|"dispatch Event"| EVT["CounterEvent"]
    EVT --> BLOC["CounterBloc (on handler)"]
    BLOC -->|"emit State"| STREAM["Stream of States"]
    STREAM -->|"BlocBuilder rebuilds"| UI
    STREAM -->|"BlocListener side-effects"| SIDE["Snackbars / Navigation"]
```

### 4.4 Master Comparison Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    Q["Need State Management?"] --> Q1{"State Local?"}
    Q1 -->|Yes| R1["Use setState()"]
    Q1 -->|No| Q2{"App Complexity?"}
    Q2 -->|Small| R2["Provider"]
    Q2 -->|Medium| R3["Riverpod"]
    Q2 -->|Enterprise| R4["BLoC"]
    R2 --> S1["ChangeNotifier + notifyListeners"]
    R3 --> S2["StateNotifier + ref.watch"]
    R4 --> S3["Event → Bloc → State Stream"]
```

### 4.5 Layered Architecture (Where Logic Lives)

```mermaid
graph TD
    L1["Presentation Layer (UI Widgets)"] --> L2["State Management Layer"]
    L2 --> L3["Domain / Business Logic Layer"]
    L3 --> L4["Data Layer (Repositories / APIs)"]
    L2 -.->|"Provider"| P["ChangeNotifier"]
    L2 -.->|"Riverpod"| R["StateNotifier"]
    L2 -.->|"BLoC"| B["Bloc + Events + States"]
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **KTU Visualization Note:** When drawing architecture in exams, always show **arrows pointing from data source → state layer → UI**. Examiners deduct marks for reverse-direction arrows.

