## 3.3 Step 3 — The Model Class (Parsing Strategy)

Before making any HTTP request, we define a **PODO (Plain Old Dart Object)** that mirrors the JSON shape. This enforces **type safety**.

```dart
// lib/models/post.dart

class Post {
  final int userId;
  final int id;
  final String title;
  final String body;

  const Post({
    required this.userId,
    required this.id,
    required this.title,
    required this.body,
  });

  /// Factory constructor — converts a JSON map into a Post instance.
  factory Post.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) {
    return Post(
      userId: json['userId'] as int,
      id: json['id'] as int,
      title: json['title'] as String,
      body: json['body'] as String,
    );
  }

  /// Serializes a Post instance back into a JSON map.
  Map<String, dynamic> toJson() {
    return {
      'userId': userId,
      'id': id,
      'title': title,
      'body': body,
    };
  }

  @override
  String toString() => 'Post(id: $id, title: $title)';
}
```

**Line-by-line derivation:**

| Line | Explanation |
|---|---|
| `final int userId` | Immutable field; promotes value semantics and widget rebuild optimization. |
| `const Post({required ...})` | `const` constructor enables compile-time constant creation (cheap). |
| `factory Post.fromJson(...)` | A factory constructor *returns* an instance — unlike generative constructors, it can return cached/subtype instances. |
| `json['userId'] as int` | Type cast; throws `TypeError` if the JSON value is null/wrong type — caught by our error handler. |

---

## 3.4 Step 4 — The API Service Layer

Encapsulating all network calls in a dedicated `ApiService` class is the **Single Responsibility Principle** in action.

```dart
// lib/services/api_service.dart

import 'dart:convert';
import 'dart:io';
import 'package:http/http.dart' as http;
import '../models/post.dart';

class ApiService {
  // The base URL is centralized; endpoints are appended per call.
  static const String _baseUrl = 'https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com';

  // Reusable HTTP client — recommended pattern.
  final http.Client _client = http.Client();

  /// GET — Fetch all posts
  Future<List<Post>> fetchPosts() async {
    final uri = Uri.parse('$_baseUrl/posts');

    try {
      final response = await _client.get(uri).timeout(
            const Duration(seconds: 10),
          );

      if (response.statusCode == 200) {
        // Step A: decode the JSON string into a Dart List
        final List<dynamic> jsonList = json.decode(response.body);

        // Step B: map each JSON object into a Post model
        return jsonList
            .map((jsonItem) => Post.fromJson(jsonItem as Map<String, dynamic>))
            .toList();
      } else {
        throw HttpException(
          'Failed to load posts. Server returned: ${response.statusCode}',
        );
      }
    } on SocketException {
      throw const SocketException('No internet connection. Please check your network.');
    } on FormatException {
      throw const FormatException('Invalid JSON format received from server.');
    } on HttpException {
      rethrow;
    } catch (e) {
      throw Exception('Unexpected error during fetchPosts: $e');
    }
  }

  /// POST — Create a new resource
  Future<Post> createPost({required String title, required String body, required int userId}) async {
    final uri = Uri.parse('$_baseUrl/posts');
    final headers = {'Content-Type': 'application/json; charset=UTF-8'};
    final payload = json.encode({
      'title': title,
      'body': body,
      'userId': userId,
    });

    try {
      final response = await _client
          .post(uri, headers: headers, body: payload)
          .timeout(const Duration(seconds: 10));

      if (response.statusCode == 201) {
        return Post.fromJson(json.decode(response.body) as Map<String, dynamic>);
      } else {
        throw HttpException('Create failed. Status: ${response.statusCode}');
      }
    } on SocketException {
      throw const SocketException('No internet connection.');
    } catch (e) {
      throw Exception('Unexpected error during createPost: $e');
    }
  }

  /// PUT — Replace an existing resource
  Future<Post> updatePost({required int id, required String title, required String body}) async {
    final uri = Uri.parse('$_baseUrl/posts/$id');
    final payload = json.encode({'title': title, 'body': body, 'userId': 1});

    final response = await _client.put(
      uri,
      headers: {'Content-Type': 'application/json'},
      body: payload,
    );

    if (response.statusCode == 200) {
      return Post.fromJson(json.decode(response.body) as Map<String, dynamic>);
    } else {
      throw HttpException('Update failed. Status: ${response.statusCode}');
    }
  }

  /// DELETE — Remove a resource
  Future<void> deletePost(int id) async {
    final uri = Uri.parse('$_baseUrl/posts/$id');
    final response = await _client.delete(uri);

    if (response.statusCode != 200 && response.statusCode != 204) {
      throw HttpException('Delete failed. Status: ${response.statusCode}');
    }
  }

  /// Always close the client when the service is disposed.
  void dispose() {
    _client.close();
  }
}
```

