## 3.7 Analytical Matrix — Async Error Handling Hierarchy

| Exception Type | Cause | Recommended Handling |
|---|---|---|
| `SocketException` | No internet / DNS failure / timeout | Show "No connection" UI with retry |
| `HttpException` | Non-2xx status code | Show server message + status code |
| `FormatException` | Malformed JSON | Log raw body, show generic parse error |
| `TimeoutException` | Request exceeded `.timeout()` | Show "Slow network" message, allow retry |
| `ClientException` | Generic client-side failure | Catch-all with error logging |
| `TypeError` | JSON value null when cast to non-nullable | Defensive coding: `as int? ?? 0` |

> **Defensive JSON Parsing Pattern** (recommended in production):
```dart
factory Post.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) {
  return Post(
    userId: json['userId'] as int? ?? 0,
    id: json['id'] as int? ?? 0,
    title: json['title'] as String? ?? 'Untitled',
    body: json['body'] as String? ?? '',
  );
}
```

