### Question 1 `[KTU University Exam – May 2024]`
**Differentiate between HTTP and HTTPS. Why is HTTPS preferred for mobile applications?**

**Model Answer:**

| Aspect | HTTP | HTTPS |
|---|---|---|
| Full Form | HyperText Transfer Protocol | HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure |
| Default Port | **80** | **443** |
| Encryption | None (plaintext) | TLS/SSL (encrypted) |
| Certificate | Not required | Requires X.509 SSL certificate |
| Speed | Marginally faster (no handshake) | Slightly slower due to TLS handshake |
| SEO Ranking | Penalized by Google | Boosted by Google |
| URL Prefix | `http://` | `https://` |

**Why HTTPS is preferred for mobile apps:**
1. **Data Confidentiality** — User credentials, OTPs, and payment data are encrypted end-to-end.
2. **Data Integrity** — TLS prevents man-in-the-middle (MITM) tampering.
3. **Authentication** — Certificates verify that the server is the genuine entity.
4. **Compliance** — App Store and Play Store policies now mandate HTTPS for sensitive APIs.
5. **Performance** — HTTP/2 (which requires HTTPS) enables multiplexing and header compression.

*(3 marks — full marks awarded for the comparison table + 2 valid reasons.)*

