> [!WARNING]
> **KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning — Common Pitfalls Where Students Lose Marks**
>
> 1. **Forgetting `await`** — Writing `http.get(url)` instead of `await http.get(url)` returns a `Future`, not a `Response`. The app will compile but crash at runtime. *(Lose 2–3 marks.)*
> 2. **Not checking `response.statusCode` before decoding** — Even an error response contains a JSON body; decoding it directly throws `FormatException`. Always check status first. *(Lose 2 marks.)*
> 3. **Missing internet permission in `AndroidManifest.xml` / `Info.plist`** — Code is correct but app crashes on real device. Examiners check this! *(Lose 1 mark.)*
> 4. **Confusing `json.encode` with `json.decode`** — Writing `decode` for outgoing requests or `encode` for incoming responses. *(Lose 2 marks.)*
> 5. **Using `setState` inside async without mounted check** — Triggers "setState called after dispose" warnings; loses UI-state marks.
> 6. **No timeout on `http.get`** — A frozen app looks like a bug; always use `.timeout(Duration(seconds: 10))`. *(Lose 1 mark.)*
> 7. **Writing `Future<List<Post>>` but returning `List<Post>` directly without `async`** — Type mismatch compile error.
> 8. **Not closing the HTTP client** in `dispose()` — Memory leak; lose marks for best practices.
> 9. **Putting API calls directly in `build()` method** — Causes infinite network calls on every rebuild. Always trigger in `initState()`. *(Lose 3 marks — major design flaw.)*
> 10. **Confusing REST with SOAP** — They are fundamentally different architectural styles; SOAP uses XML envelopes while REST uses resource URIs and standard HTTP verbs.

