# 5. KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

## 5.1 Part A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Q1. `[KTU University Exam – Model Paper 2024]`
**Define state management in mobile applications. List any two popular state management approaches in Flutter with one-line use cases.**

**Model Answer (10 lines):**

State management is the process of handling changes to the application's data over time and ensuring the UI reflects the current state in a predictable and efficient manner. It involves *holding*, *mutating*, and *propagating* state to dependent UI components.

Two popular Flutter state management approaches:
1. **`setState()`** — Used inside a `StatefulWidget` for state local to a single widget (e.g., a checkbox toggle).
2. **`Provider` with `ChangeNotifier`** — Used for app-wide state shared across multiple screens (e.g., logged-in user, cart items).

> [!NOTE]
> Word count guideline for 3-mark answers: **8–12 lines**. Going below 6 lines costs marks.

---

### Q2. `[KTU University Exam – Model Paper 2024]`
**What is data persistence? Compare `SharedPreferences` and `sqflite` in terms of data type, capacity, and best use case.**

**Model Answer:**

Data persistence is the ability of an application to retain data beyond a single app session, so that it survives app closure and device restarts.

| Criterion | `SharedPreferences` | `sqflite` |
|---|---|---|
| Data type | Primitive key–value (bool, int, double, String, `List<String>`) | Structured relational tables (rows & columns) |
| Capacity | < 1 MB recommended | GB scale |
| Best use case | Theme, language, login flags | User-generated content like notes, expenses |

