**Q2. [KTU University Exam – Model Question, PECST695 Milestone Series]**

**Explain the role of Firebase Authentication in a mobile application. List any two Firebase services other than Authentication.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

**Role of Firebase Authentication (1 mark):**
Firebase Authentication provides a ready-made, secure backend service for user sign-in and sign-up. It supports multiple providers (email/password, Google, Facebook, phone OTP) and returns a JWT ID token that can be used to authenticate subsequent API calls or authorize Firestore access via Security Rules.

**Two other Firebase services (2 marks — 1 each):**
1. **Cloud Firestore** — A real-time NoSQL document database that syncs data across devices within milliseconds.
2. **Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)** — Enables sending push notifications and remote messages to targeted users or topics.

