### 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Rapid Revision Checklist)

✅ **Milestone 3 = State Management + Persistence + API/Firebase.**

✅ **State Management** answers: *"Where does the data live and how does UI learn it changed?"* — SSOT, Read-Only, Pure Mutations.

✅ **Provider** = `ChangeNotifier` + `notifyListeners()` + `context.watch/read`.

✅ **Riverpod** = Provider's testable, compile-safe successor — higher viva marks if mentioned.

✅ **Bloc** = Event → State via Streams — preferred in enterprise Flutter projects.

✅ **SharedPreferences** = small primitive key-value pairs only (theme, flags, auth token).

✅ **SQLite/Room** = structured relational data; **ALWAYS use parameterized queries** to prevent SQL injection.

✅ **Hive** = fast NoSQL local DB for Dart objects.

✅ **REST = Resources + HTTP Verbs + JSON.** GET is safe & idempotent; POST is neither.

✅ **HTTP Status Codes:** 2xx success, 3xx redirect, 4xx client fault, 5xx server fault.

✅ **Idempotency** = calling an operation N times = calling it once. Critical for retry logic.

✅ **JWT (JSON Web Token)** = compact token format used for stateless API authentication.

✅ **Firebase Authentication** supports email/password, Google, Facebook, phone OTP, Apple.

✅ **Cloud Firestore** = real-time NoSQL document database; uses `snapshots()` for live streams.

✅ **`FieldValue.serverTimestamp()`** — always prefer this over client-side timestamps.

✅ **Real-time UI** uses `StreamBuilder` + `snapshots()` — no manual refresh needed.

✅ **Offline-First Strategy** = local DB (Hive/SQLite) as source of truth + sync with cloud when online.

✅ **Always handle:** `DioException`, `SocketException`, `TimeoutException`, `FirebaseAuthException`.

✅ **WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized()** is mandatory before `Firebase.initializeApp()`.

✅ **Clean Architecture Layers:** Presentation → Domain → Data (Local + Remote Sources).

✅ **Repository Pattern** = single abstraction over Local + Remote data sources.

✅ **JSON Serialization** can be manual (`fromJson/toJson`) or auto (`json_serializable`, `freezed`).

✅ **For KTU viva:** Be ready to draw the architecture diagram from memory and justify each layer's purpose.

